 • Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa met a delegation of leaders of political parties who did not have an opportunity at the meeting at Parliament to deliver statements of support. The leaders sent messages of support to the public. Various ministers met with the president on Sunday in an effort to solidify a strategy to curb the spread of the virus. READ: Presidency denies lockdown rumours Currently, in South Africa there are 240 confirmed COVID-19 cases. Worldwide, that figure has surpassed the 308,000 mark.